All Implemented Interfaces:
Subscriber<ConfigObject>, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.Scrollable
public class ObjectEditorPanel
extends ScrollablePanel
implements Subscriber<ConfigObject>

Used to edit the distributed object fields of a particular configuration object. When the panel is first shown, it will subscribe to the object and display its fields. It will not automatically unsubscribe when it is hidden, but rather cleanup() must be called to let it know that it's not going to be shown again soon and it is safe for it to clear out its subscription.

See Also:
ConfigEditorPanel, Serialized Form
